headline: Sultan Qaboos Dies at 79; Built Oman Into Prosperous Oasis of Peacemaking
abstract: The longest-serving Arab ruler, Qaboos pulled his nation from poverty and brokered quiet talks between global foes.
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT, Lebanon â€” Sultan Qaboos bin Said of Oman, who over nearly five decades in power transformed his Persian Gulf kingdom from an isolated enclave into a developed nation known for brokering quiet talks between global foes, has died, the Omani government announced on Saturday. He was 79.
